les\n\n1. Preserve exact payloads, tokens, cookies, headers, URLs, query strings, and request bodies character-for-character.\n2. Preserve exact evidence snippets that prove exploitation or validation.\n3. If a detail is missing, write `Not observed` instead of guessing.\n4. Separate confirmed facts from unconfirmed leads.\n5. Prefer the latest supervisor synthesis when it provides concrete reproduction steps, proof, or PoC details.\n6. Do not hide failed attempts if they explain preconditions, blockers, or why a PoC works only in a specific form.\n7. Write the report under `reports/` with a filename derived from the application or target name plus the primary vulnerability type, using lowercase kebab-case.\n\n## What Matters Most\n\nExtract and prioritize, in this order:\n\n1. Validation tokens, flags, secrets, or other proof strings matching `Information`\n2. Exact reproduction steps\n3. Exact PoC payloads and HTTP requests\n4. Tool evidence and response snippets proving impact\n5. Target information and affected endpoints\n6. Remediation and concrete fix guidance\n\n## Required Output Format\n\nYour report MUST use the following section order and headings:\n\n```markdown\n## TL;DR\n- Objective:\n- Outcome:\n- Highest-impact finding:\n- Validation status:\n\n## Target Information\n- Target:\n- Host / base URL:\n- Application or component:\n- Authentication context:\n- Relevant technology details:\n\n## Confirmed Vulnerability\n### [Vulnerability name or `Not observed`]\n- Affected endpoint / component:\n- Impact:\n- Preconditions:\n- Exact payload or PoC:\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n1. [Exact step]\n2. [Exact step]\n3. [Exact step]\n\n## Validation / Evidence\n- Validation token / flag:\n- Tool evidence:\n- Request evidence:\n- Response evidence:\n- Notes on reliability / limitations:\n\n## Remediation\n- Root cause:\n- Recommended fix:\n- Defense-in-depth:\n\n## How to Verify the Fix\n1. [Concrete validation step]\n2. [Expected secure result]\n\n## Remaining Leads\